{
  "article_id": "Yates1907",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "SAN NICHOLAS ISLAND",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of the group of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is about nine miles in length and four in width; water is plentiful; was formerly densely populated, but now is a treeless waste—the result of fire and the pasturage of sheep."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "We learn by tradition that the",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Alaska Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who were placed upon",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to trade with",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", killed off the male inhabitants and took possession.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In 1835"
      },
      {
        "text": "the padres",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sent"
      },
      {
        "text": "a vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to remove the women and children."
      },
      {
        "text": "This was accomplished, with the exception of",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one woman",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who jumped into the surf and swam ashore to hunt for",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had accidentally been left behind.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The next we hear of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "lone woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was in 1850, after a lapse of fifteen years.,"
      },
      {
        "text": "when",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", visited",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and discovered traces of recent habitation; but it was not until 1853 that the",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "female Robinson Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found and removed to",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where from the sudden and complete change of manner of living, she soon died.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She had outlived",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her people",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and found no one able to converse with her in her almost forgotten language. It is supposed she was the last of",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "; her clothing, made from skins, and needles of bone, were deposited in",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Vatican",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "mu_vaticanmuseum",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", at",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "But the incidents connected with her stay upon and removal from",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "will soon be forgotten, although the refuse heaps of",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "its former inhabitants",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "will remain as evidence of",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a lost people",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Who can realize the utter and wretched loneliness of the"
      },
      {
        "text": "poor creature",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who spent eighteen years among the deserted homes of"
      },
      {
        "text": "her ancestors",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where the ground was whitened by their bleaching bones?"
      }
    ]
  ]
}